This is an Distributted Application using MQTT protocol and socket with tcp for communication
For more information see: https://paulo-coelho.github.io/ds_notes/projeto/

Dependencies:

	Install mosquitto MQTT broker - https://mosquitto.org/download/

	Install python 3.10.2 - https://www.python.org/downloads/

	Install python dependencies:
		python -m pip install --upgrade pip
		pip install configparser - https://pypi.org/project/configparser/
		pip install paho-mqtt - https://pypi.org/project/paho-mqtt/


		the next 2 should be installed by default and will cause instalation only errors if already installed:
			pip install hashlib - https://pypi.org/project/hashlib/
			pip install hmac - https://pypi.org/project/hmac/:

Configuration:

	Since this app executes in shell with a characters box:
		set the terminal font type to a monospace one
		the characters box is wrapped by unicode charactes, verify if your shell recognizes:
			â–ˆ - U+2588 Full Block
			â–€ - U+2580 Upper Half Block
			â–„ - U+2584 Lower Half Block

	In config.ini, to change config variables:
		[mqtt_connection]
		host - MQTT broker host used
		port - MQTT broker port used

		[screen]
		line_size - how many characters per line
		indent_n - indent size